summary: So I know a long time ago a discussion was raised about young people in the GFFA idolizing bounty hunters. But imagine like...
body:
So I know a long time ago a discussion was raised about young people in the GFFA idolizing bounty hunters. But imagine like fandom levels of idolization. Like kids that steal and hang wanted posters on their bedroom walls, like they would a boy band. Like kids that write fanfiction and self-inserts and imagines with their hunter crush. Like kids that would swarm their faves in public for pics and autographs.

Idk I just think fandom culture in the GFFA would be an interesting topic to explore.

summary: Like look JJ is not as subtle at story telling as Rian is and sure he misses some of the nuances but that man is a total...
body:
Like look JJ is not as subtle at story telling as Rian is and sure he misses some of the nuances but that man is a total romantic who laid the ground work for Reylo.

The idea that JJ didn’t know Rian was going to move the love story forward is ridiculous. He was a producer on TLJ. The major story lines have been set from before TFA came out. No one writing/making these movies is ~changing~ major story arch plot lines, just how they get there. Eg; even if JJ didn’t intend to kill Luke, Rian did so knowing Luke could come back as a force ghost to meet the laid out plot points, etc.

It blows my mind that people think Rian like– hijacked the story line and no one at LF said anything like THATS NOT HOW THIS WORKS.

summary: Finn Meta Week Day 5: Finn’s Future I’m way behind the past days, because my sched is busy and my health is weird but anyways,...
body:
Finn Meta Week Day 5: Finn’s Future

I’m way behind the past days, because my sched is busy and my health is weird but anyways, here is my entry for day 5 of Finn Meta Week by @finnappreciation, Finn’s future.

I really wanted Finn to have a bright future. He is a hero and deserves it so much. His intelligence, courage and his special ability to draw others to him will make him a perfect General. As heavily implied in Before the Awakening, he is good at leading and making strategies (even Captain Phasma is impressed by him).  While being a General, he may also help Rey train possible future padawans since he is also force sensitive and is good at handling lightsabers.

In the Final battle against the First Order, Finn will be part of the lead but will volunteer to fight and may even come face to face against his abusers, General Hux and/or Kylo Ren. Personally, I want him to face General Hux, the man who played a major part in the First Order reconditioning. He may also lead some sort of a Stormtrooper Rebellion and put an end to Hux. After that, he helps Rey defeat Kylo Ren and the Knights of Ren in an epic battle that will put an end to the First Order.

I also believe that one day, after the war has ended, he will meet his true family (I’m really praying that the WOC casting call is his sister) and/or make his own family with someone that he really loves and loves him back (Personally, I want him with Rey).

That’s all for now. This is my personal opinion and I just hope for the best for his character in episode IX. :D

summary: The Reylo AU I didn’t know I needed...
title: The Reylo AU I didn’t know I needed...
body: where Rey is a reporter/writer for National Geographic and a surly Ben her designated Photographer. Together they spend a week among nomads in Kyrgyzstan and while Rey easily bonds with the people there, even though she doesn’t understand a single word being said, Ben just sticks out like a sore thumb bickering with Rey about how she should stop playing tag with the kids and instead focus on why they are there in the first place. So basically them arguing the entire time, grumpy Ben and a happy Rey somewhere in the Plains of Kyrgyzstan….
